article.headline: Md.-Eastern Shore 62, N. Carolina A&amp,T 52
article.story: GREENSBORO, N.C. -- Hillary Haley scored 20 points to lead Maryland-Eastern Shore to a 62-52 win over North Carolina A&T on Monday night. Tim Burns finished with 13 points and four steals for the Hawks (7-16, 5-5 Mid-Eastern Athletic Conference), while Tyler Hines added 12 points and 12 rebounds. The Hawks used a 10-0 run in the second half to jump out to a 47-36 lead after a layup from Haley with 11:34 remaining in the game. A layup from Burns gave the Hawks their largest lead of the game at 52-38 with 9:12 left in the game, and the Aggies never got any closer than within eight points the rest of the way. Dwane Joshua scored 19 points to lead the Aggies (8-16, 4-6). The Hawks shot 42.3 percent from the field in the second half (11-for-26). The Aggies shot 30.4 percent in the second half (7-for-23).
